{# TITLE: Coumadin Care Center #}<h2>Outpatient Anticoagulant Clinic</h2>
<p><b>Overview of Coumadin</b>&nbsp;</p>
<p>CoumadinTM is an oral anticoagulant medication, commonly referred to as a blood thinner. The generic name for Coumadin is Sodium Warfarin. Coumadin is used to prevent the formation of blood clots that can cause heart attack, stroke, or blood vessel blockages in various parts of the body. Many patients are prescribed Coumadin or other anticoagulant medications because they have conditions that increase their risk of blood clot-related complications, such as atrial fibrillation, deep vein thrombosis (DVT), pulmonary embolism, acute myocardial infarction (heart attack), coronary artery disease, heart failure, valvular heart disease, cardiomyopathy, and peripheral vascular disease.&nbsp;</p>
